Job Responsibilities

Assist in developing 360 digital marketing strategies, plan and drive implementation of digital marketing campaigns and digital ecosystem development to achieve business goals;
Work with internal and external parties to build digital & data infrastructure and facilitate smooth digital transformation;
Develop and manage digital platforms, including website, eShop, social media, media advertising, KOL/influencer and other channels to drive multi-touch point consumer engagement;
Develop strategic social media plan and work with agencies to deliver quality content to audiences and enhance brand presence, acquire fans and achieve business targets;
Ensure all digital communications are conveyed in a way that contributes to master brand image building and master campaign message delivery;
Prepare insightful and actionable brief and collaborate closely with agencies to drive quality output to achieve defined business and marketing objectives;
Regularly track and analyze digital performance, involving website, eShop (e.g. new customer acquisition, sales conversion), and provide cross-analysis of the results and insights for continuous improvement of digital marketing programs;
Drive ecommerce business & CRM program, monitor and review daily operations, analyze consumer journey and keyword strategy to improve UIUX & SEO on the brand websites & eShops retention tactics for improvement;
Monitor budgets & and campaign KPIs for ROI improvement;
Assist in other marketing duties and handle ad hoc tasks as assigned.

Requirements

Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Marketing, Advertising, eCommerce or related disciplines;
3 years of solid work experience in digital marketing;
Digital-savvy and knowledgeable on the latest digital trends;
Strong desire to learn and ability to multi-task;
Self-motivated, proactive and willing to take challenges;
Good communication, presentation and interpersonal skills;
Strong project management & organizational skills;
Less experienced candidates may be considered as Senior Digital Marketing Executive.

